AN INJURED woman has been hoisted to safety after plunging 10ft down a steep embankment.
Fire crews used ropes to rescue the woman - who suffered a suspected broken leg - at Calderglen Country Park in East Kilbride, South Lanarkshire.
She was treated on scene by paramedics before being taken to hospital.
An air ambulance was also scrambled to the country park just after 4.30pm but was stood down soon after.
